@page "/faq"
@layout Layout.BaseLayout

<div class="faq-container">
    <div class="faq-header">
        <h2>FAQ</h2>
        <p>Quick guidance for creating, finding, and editing canvases in Linteum.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-grid">
        <section class="faq-section">
            <h4>What is this project?</h4>
            <p>
                Linteum is a collaborative pixel-canvas web app where users can create canvases, subscribe to existing canvases,
                and place or update pixels together in real time.
            </p>
            <p>
                Your subscribed canvases appear in the left sidebar, so the fastest way to jump between projects is to keep
                your active canvases subscribed.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="faq-section">
            <h4>How do I create a Canvas?</h4>
            <p>
                Open <strong>Add new canvas</strong> in the sidebar and provide a canvas name, width, and height.
                You can also set an optional password if you want controlled access.
            </p>
            <p>
                After creation, the canvas is added to your subscriptions and appears in the sidebar list.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="faq-section">
            <h4>How do I subscribe to an existing Canvas?</h4>
            <p>
                Use <strong>Subscribe to canvas</strong> in the sidebar, enter the canvas name, and provide a password only if it is protected.
            </p>
            <p>
                As an example, you can check out the <strong>VanGogh</strong> canvas.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="faq-section">
            <h4>How does pixel changing work?</h4>
            <p>
                Open a subscribed canvas, choose a color, and place a pixel in the canvas grid.
                Pixel updates are collaborative, so you can work together on images with other users.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="faq-section faq-wide">
            <h4>Common scenarios</h4>
            <p>
                <strong>Scenario 1:</strong> Create a private canvas with a password for a small team sketch session.
            </p>
            <p>
                <strong>Scenario 2:</strong> Subscribe to a public canvas like <strong>VanGogh</strong> or <strong>Levitan</strong> or <strong>Thailand</strong> and contribute pixel-by-pixel details.
            </p>
            <p>
                <strong>Scenario 3:</strong> Keep a few canvases subscribed and switch quickly through the sidebar while editing.
            </p>
        </section>
        <section class="faq-section faq-wide">
            <h4>Source code &amp; Contact</h4>
            <p>
                The project's source code is available on GitHub:
                <a href="https://github.com/DAnikeyev/Linteum" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://github.com/DAnikeyev/Linteum</a>
            </p>
            <p>
                For questions or issues, contact the maintainer:
                <a href="mailto:dmitry.anikeyev@gmail.com">dmitry.anikeyev@gmail.com</a>
            </p>
        </section>
    </div>
</div>
